      {
        "id": "09d161a70f09249cacc061c7d017a83fdd106f20",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 653,
          "name": "Ofir Sonsino",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ofirson@gmail.com",
          "username": "os0695"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-02-25 15:09:18.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThanks for clarifying Michael.\nDo you know whether these possible implementations are already integrated to SO?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "aaa095017c39c5ff0637982915d1f6b6d87e2ec9",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5269,
          "name": "Michael Morris",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "michael.morris@est.tech",
          "username": "MichaelMorris"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-02-25 15:33:05.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHi Ofir, I dont think there would be any existing flows or building blocks in SO that would use them, but that is not to say they couldnt be added. \nAs a service design tool though I dont think SDC should be tied to SO, the vnf and service packages it creates can be consumed by any client that adheres to the same model, be that SO or a different orchestrator capable of handling ONAP or ETSI compliant packages",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "a604098d02270abcd527f78e6e16b75a1513292c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5269,
          "name": "Michael Morris",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "michael.morris@est.tech",
          "username": "MichaelMorris"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-02-28 08:45:23.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHi Ofir, Yuli, do you have any further concerns on this issue or can it be merged",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "83f64387887c0f4b207062a4609f79fb1de2e7bb",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 653,
          "name": "Ofir Sonsino",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ofirson@gmail.com",
          "username": "os0695"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-03-01 10:11:58.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nSorry I'll be out of office until Wednesday, I'll update upon my return. \nOverall SDC is part of ONAP and not a standalone design tool. Therefore it's expected that SO would support SDC design capabilities, otherwise there's no point for these capabilities from project perspective.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "3dbc0a4bd9f2b1d6bcc58057fa73e585e3d720c6",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5269,
          "name": "Michael Morris",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "michael.morris@est.tech",
          "username": "MichaelMorris"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-03-04 09:47:15.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThere are no code updates needed in SO to make use of this as SO has a plugable architecture. Anybody can write a building block that can be deployed into SO to take advantage of this (or any other) feature.\nAlso, SO can pass a VNF package to a VNFM through the vnfm adapter, in which case the VNFD is handled by the VNFM. The VNFM may make use of this feature",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "206b6a6b18377e3691c080a618ebba118f3ad77d",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 653,
          "name": "Ofir Sonsino",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ofirson@gmail.com",
          "username": "os0695"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-03-15 17:10:31.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI agree\n@Yuli please assist with code review then we can merge",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
